abstract.value: <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Camels Coming</title> was a small avant garde poetry magazine in operation from the mid-1960's through the early 1970's. The <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Camels Coming</title>Archive is a collection of correspondence written to the editor, Richard Morris, and includes manuscripts of material submitted for publication in <title ns2:type="simple" render="italic">Camels Coming</title>.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the following form: <lb/><lb/>Identification of item, date (if known); The Camels Coming Archive; MSS 009; box number; folder number; <address><addressline>Fales Library and Special Collections</addressline></address>, New York University Libraries.
The <title type="simple" render="italic">Camels Coming</title> Archive was purchased from Gotham Books (New York) in 1970.

<list><item>Andre, Michael. "Tooth and Claw, Tums and Nicotine Patches: [review of] 'The Evolutionists' by Richard Morris." Exquisite Corpse, #11(2002). accessed 8 Jan. 2003. [http://www.corpse.org/issue_11/critiques/andre.html].</item><item></item><item></item><item></item></list>

Series I: Correspondence and Manuscripts: contains 2 boxes of correspondence and manuscripts submitted to the editor, Richard Morris. Noted correspondents and contributors include Clayton Eshleman, Carol Berge, Paul Blackburn Robert Bly, Barbara Holland, Ted Enslin, Michael McClure, and Gary Snyder. An inventory (box 1, folder 1) is included with more detailed information regarding the correspondence. Items from other small press publishers is also prevalent in the collection (i.e. Al Young, and Clayton Eshleman).
